<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Avil Page (Posts about amazing facts about patents)</title><link>http://www.avilpage.com</link><description></description><atom:link rel="self" href="http://www.avilpage.com/categories/amazing-facts-about-patents.xml" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Wed, 01 Feb 2017 15:35:34 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>16 Most Interesting Facts About Patents!</title><link>http://www.avilpage.com/2014/02/16-most-interesting-facts-about-patents.html</link><dc:creator>Chillar Anand</dc:creator><description>&lt;div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on"&gt;&lt;ol style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;Halliburton Company once tried to patent patenting. – &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://boingboing.net/2008/11/17/halliburton-tries-to.html" style="-webkit-transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out; background-color: white; border: 0px none; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px; list-style: none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;Microsoft has a patent, for opening a new window when you click a hyperlink that expires in 2021 –&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.google.com/patents/US7114128" style="-webkit-transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out; background-color: white; border: 0px none; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px; list-style: none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;Amazon holds a patent on 1-click buying; Apple pays them licensing fees – &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1-Click" style="-webkit-transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out; background-color: white; border: 0px none; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px; list-style: none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;As Apple is granted “Slide-to-Unlock” patent, they in a case against Motorola also argued “a tap is a zero-length swipe.” – &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://gigaom.com/mobile/famous-judge-spikes-apple-google-case-calls-patent-system-dysfunctional/" rel="nofollow" style="-webkit-transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out; background-color: white; border: 0px none; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px; list-style: none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;Abraham Lincoln is the only U.S. president to receive a patent while in the office. He was awarded patent No. 6,469 in May 1849 for a device designed to lift boats off the sand bars. – &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abraham_Lincoln%27s_patent" style="-webkit-transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out; background-color: white; border: 0px none; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px; list-style: none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;In 1945, a radar engineer, Percy Spencer while working at Ratheon stepped in front of a magnetron, a device that powers radars. He noticed a chocolate bar in his pocket had melted. Later that year, he filed a patent for the first microwave oven. – &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://invention.smithsonian.org/centerpieces/iap/inventors_spe.html" style="-webkit-transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out; background-color: white; border: 0px none; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px; list-style: none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;There is a patent for a surgical procedure to implant semiconductors into eyes to give humans night vision like Deus Ex and Riddick. – &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.wipo.int/patentscope/search/en/WO2008106605" style="-webkit-transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out; background-color: white; border: 0px none; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px; list-style: none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;In the mid-1800s France gave out an important patent in photography for free as a gift to the world except for Britain. They were made to pay. – &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Louis_Daguerre#Competition_with_Talbot" style="-webkit-transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out; background-color: white; border: 0px none; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px; list-style: none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;There is a patent troll company that claims ownership on WIFI sharing. It has being suing small businesses and hotels for the last couple of years. – &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://arstechnica.com/tech-policy/2013/02/wi-fi-patent-troll-hit-with-novel-anti-racketeering-charges-emerges-unscathed/" style="-webkit-transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out; background-color: white; border: 0px none; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px; list-style: none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;For unknown reasons, during a bidding war with a consortium of tech firms for Nortel’s 6,000 patents, Google bid $1,902,160,540, then $2,614,972,128, and eventually $3.14159 billion (references to Brun’s constant, Meissel–Mertens constant, and pi) – &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nortel#cite_ref-Google-PatentSale_104-0" style="-webkit-transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out; background-color: white; border: 0px none; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px; list-style: none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;When Marconi, who is erroneously cited as the “Inventor of Radio”, attempted to get a patent in the US, he was repeatedly turned down because Tesla already held the patent. In 1904, however, Marconi’s patent was inexplicably granted, and Tesla died broke. – &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.pbs.org/tesla/ll/ll_whoradio.html" style="-webkit-transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out; background-color: white; border: 0px none; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px; list-style: none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;In 1955, Jonas Salk chose not to patent his polio vaccine for the sake of humanity. If he would have patented it he would have earned an estimated $7 billion. – &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.forbes.com/sites/quora/2012/08/09/how-much-money-did-jonas-salk-potentially-forfeit-by-not-patenting-the-polio-vaccine.com" style="-webkit-transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out; background-color: white; border: 0px none; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px; list-style: none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;The inventor of the Laser, Gordon Gould fought with both the US Patent office and Laser manufacturers for a period of 38 years before finally achieving the right to both obtain and enforce patents covering the Laser technology he had invented. – &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gordon_Gould" style="-webkit-transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out; background-color: white; border: 0px none; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px; list-style: none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;No one really knows who invented the fire hydrant, because its patent perished in a fire. – &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fire_hydrant" style="-webkit-transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out; background-color: white; border: 0px none; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px; list-style: none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;WD-40 ( &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19.190340042114258px;"&gt;a lubricant, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: inherit;"&gt;penetrating oil&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19.190340042114258px;"&gt; and water-displacing spray. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;) is not patent protected, thereby avoiding completely disclosing its ingredients, making it harder for any other companies to mimic. – &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wd-40#Formulation" style="-webkit-transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out; background-color: white; border: 0px none; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px; list-style: none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: white; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px;"&gt;The movie industry is based in Hollywood on the west coast because movie makers were trying to get away from Thomas Edison (based in New Jersey). He had patents covering virtually all the movie making process and the Ninth Circuit Court of Appeals in California was known to rule against patent claims. –&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Motion_Picture_Patents_Company" style="background-color: white; border: 0px none; font-family: inherit; line-height: 19px; list-style: none; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; text-decoration: none;"&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Credit: &lt;a href="http://kickassfacts.com/" target="_blank"&gt;Kickassfacts&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>amazing facts about patents</category><category>apple patent facts</category><category>funny patent facts</category><category>interesting facts about patents</category><category>Microsoft patent facts</category><category>patent facts</category><category>patents statistics</category><category>weird patent facts</category><guid>http://www.avilpage.com/2014/02/16-most-interesting-facts-about-patents.html</guid><pubDate>Mon, 24 Feb 2014 08:38:00 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>